    intro: "Start-ups don't fail because of bad ideas. They fail because of bad execution. They build the wrong MVP, burn cash on features nobody wants, pick technology that can't scale, and run out of runway before they find product-market fit. A geek who's been through this a hundred times can compress your learning curve from years to months. That's not a nice-to-have—it's the difference between your start-up and a statistic.",
