          { question: "How long does technical due diligence take?", answer: "A thorough technical DD assessment typically takes 5-10 business days, depending on the complexity of the technology. Jeff Cline can provide expedited assessments in 3-5 business days for time-sensitive deals. The assessment includes codebase review, architecture analysis, team interviews, and a comprehensive written report." },
          { question: "How much does technical due diligence cost compared to a bad investment?", answer: "Technical DD typically costs $15-50K depending on scope. Considering that the average failed technology investment loses investors $1-10M+, the ROI on proper DD is enormous. One prevented bad investment pays for decades of DD assessments." },
          { question: "What are the most common red flags found during technical due diligence?", answer: "The five most common red flags are: technical debt that will require major rewrites to scale, architecture that can't support projected growth, key-person dependency where one developer is the entire technical team, security vulnerabilities that create liability, and technology claims that don't match reality (e.g., 'proprietary AI' that's actually commodity tools)." },
          { question: "Should I do technical due diligence on every deal?", answer: "For any deal where technology is a significant component of value—which is most deals today—yes. The depth can be scaled: a lighter assessment for smaller checks, comprehensive DD for larger investments. Jeff Cline offers tiered DD packages to match investment size and risk profile." }
